HEADWORD: Scotale
<hw>Scot"ale</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>,
}</mhw> <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Scot</ets> + <ets>ale</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(O. Eng. Law)</fld> <def>The keeping of an alehouse by an officer
of a forest, and drawing people to spend their money for liquor, for
fear of his displeasure.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

